Metropolitan Area: MSA/Micro Area name from Census (all sizes)
State: State abbreviation (e.g., CA, TX, NY) - extracted from MSA name
Advanced Degree Growth (CAGR %): 5-year CAGR from 2018 to 2023 of advanced degree holders
Tech Wage Growth (CAGR %): CAGR of total quarterly wages for NAICS 5415+5182 (Q3 2023 - Q2 2025)
Latest Quarterly Tech Wages ($): Total tech sector wages in Q2 2025
Tech Employment: Tech sector employment count (month 3 of Q2 2025)
Tech Establishments: Number of tech establishments in Q2 2025
Affordability Score (0-100): Min-max normalized inverse of (home value / San Jose home value)
Rental Cash Flow Score (0-100): Min-max normalized inverse of Price-to-Rent ratio. Lower P/R = higher score
State Unemployment Rate (%): Latest state-level unemployment rate from FRED (Federal Reserve Economic Data)
Zillow Home Value (Latest): Zillow Home Value Index (ZHVI) - Most recent month
Zillow Rent (Latest Monthly): Zillow Observed Rent Index (ZORI) - Monthly rent
Price-to-Rent Ratio: Home price / (Annual rent). Lower = better cash flow

Rank: LOWER rank = BETTER overall opportunity. Rank 1 is the top market combining growth + cash flow + affordability
Metropolitan Area: The geographic market. Research local regulations, property taxes, and landlord-tenant laws for this area
State: Use to filter markets by state. Consider state income tax, property tax rates, landlord-friendly laws (TX, FL, AZ = favorable)
Boom Score: HIGHER = BETTER. Scores 70+ are excellent. Combines tech growth (appreciation) + rental returns (cash flow)
Median Home Value: HIGHER = More upfront capital needed. Compare to your budget. $200-400k = accessible, $400k+ = premium
Indian Population (2018): Baseline high-income community size. HIGHER = established demand base for quality rentals
Indian Population (2023): Current high-income community. HIGHER = larger tenant pool for premium properties
Indian Pop Growth (CAGR %): HIGHER = Faster influx of high-income residents. 50%+ = strong migration trend, demand increasing
Advanced Degrees (2018): Baseline educated workforce. HIGHER = stable job market, less economic volatility
Advanced Degrees (2023): Current educated workforce. HIGHER = strong knowledge economy, higher income tenants available
Advanced Degree Growth (CAGR %): HIGHER = Growing talent pool. Positive growth = expanding opportunities, attracts employers
Tech Wage Growth (CAGR %): HIGHER = Expanding tech sector. 10%+ = strong growth, 50%+ = boom. Drives future appreciation
Latest Quarterly Tech Wages ($): Total tech payroll. HIGHER = bigger tech economy, more stable. $500M+ = substantial sector
Tech Employment: Number of tech workers. HIGHER = more diverse sector, less dependent on single employer
Tech Establishments: Number of tech companies. HIGHER = healthier ecosystem, not dominated by one company
Median Household Income: HIGHER = Wealthier residents, can charge higher rents. $75k+ = strong market, $100k+ = premium
Tech Wage Score (0-100): Relative tech growth rank. HIGHER = faster growth vs. other markets. 70+ = top quartile
Indian Pop Score (0-100): Combines population size + growth. HIGHER = better scale + momentum. 70+ = excellent
Affordability Score (0-100): Relative to San Jose ($1.34M). HIGHER = cheaper entry point. 70+ = very affordable
Rental Cash Flow Score (0-100): Based on Price-to-Rent ratio. HIGHER = better rental returns. 70+ = strong cash flow market
State Unemployment Rate (%): LOWER = Better. Under 4% = excellent job market. Over 6% = weak economy, higher vacancy risk
Zillow Home Value (Latest): Current market price. Compare to Census value to see if prices rising/falling. Use for deal analysis
Zillow Rent (Latest Monthly): HIGHER = Better gross income. Multiply by 12 for annual rent. Use to calculate cash-on-cash return
Price-to-Rent Ratio: LOWER = BETTER cash flow. Under 15 = good buy-and-hold. 12-13 = excellent. Over 20 = rent don't buy
